creator: Jacob & Wilhelm Grimm
description:
LibriVox recording of Grimm's Fairy Tales - Retold in One-Syllable Words by Jacob & Wilhelm Grimm.
Read in English by Doug Fajardo; Katie Rose; Sharon Handy; Mike Harris; Brandon Fletcher; Christie Crews; Jude; Shakira Searle; Evan Pierce; Kathy Hulick
The stories we have read and loved but retold in words of one syllable to make it easier for young readers or those where English is a second language. Some you will know and love, others you may never have heard of but all are worth reading and listening to. Hansel and Grethel, The Wold and the Six Little Kids; 3 tales about elves; Snow White and Rose Red; King Roughbeard; The Frog Prince; Cinderella; Little Red Cap (little REd Riding Hood) and The Goose Girl are only a few of these delightful tales. - Summary by Phil chenevert
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
